race.comment: Good little race. SCILLATO (11) did some nice things last time in, winning a good 3yo open race at Flemington three starts back. Wide draw here but has plenty of upside and will be very hard to hold out. with any natural improvement down in the weights. PROVED (1) is hard to knock given she's unbeaten in five starts. She does everything right up on speed but does have to give some handy types some weight. She may be good enough regardless and maps well. LET'SFACETHEMUSIC (7) resumes. He can mix his form but has run well in some strong races and draws well. Respecting. HARRY'S YACHT (3) resumes. 1100m is a touch short of his best trip but he put up some big performances last time in and can sprint well fresh.
